<?xml version="1.0"?>
<section xml:id="ch-loops">
    <title>Review - Loops</title>
    <introduction>
        <p>Practice tracing <c>for</c> and <c>while</c> loops, predicting output, and writing loops for repetition.</p>
    </introduction>
    <subsection>
        <title>Part A: How Many Times?</title>
        <exercise xml:id="ex-loop-count">
            <statement>
                <p>Determine how many times each loop runs.</p>
                <program language="python">
for i in range(5):
    print(i)</program>
                <program language="python">
count = 0
while count &lt; 3:
    print(count)
    count += 1</program>
            </statement>
            <response>
            </response>
        </exercise>
    </subsection>
    <subsection>
        <title>Part B: Trace the Loop</title>
        <exercise xml:id="ex-loop-trace">
            <statement>
                <program language="python">
total = 0
for num in [2, 4, 6]:
    total = total + num</program>
                <p>Trace the values of <c>num</c> and <c>total</c> at each iteration.</p>
            </statement>
            <response>
            </response>
        </exercise>
    </subsection>
    <subsection>
        <title>Part C: Predict the Output</title>
        <exercise xml:id="ex-loop-output">
            <statement>
                <p>What is printed by each loop?</p>
                <program language="python">
for ch in "cat":
    print(ch)</program>
                <program language="python">
x = 1
while x &lt;= 3:
    print(x)
    x += 1</program>
            </statement>
            <response>
            </response>
        </exercise>
    </subsection>
    <subsection>
        <title>Part D: Spot the Problem</title>
        <exercise xml:id="ex-loop-problem">
            <statement>
                <program language="python">
count = 1
while count &lt;= 5:
    print(count)</program>
                <p>Explain what is wrong with this loop.</p>
            </statement>
            <response>
            </response>
        </exercise>
    </subsection>
    <subsection>
        <title>Part E: Create</title>
        <exercise xml:id="ex-loop-create">
            <statement>
                <p>Write a <c>for</c> loop that prints each value in the list <c>[1, 2, 3, 4]</c>. Write a <c>while</c> loop that prints the numbers <c>1</c> through <c>5</c>. Then write a loop that counts how many letters are in the string <c>&quot;hello&quot;</c>.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <program language="python" interactive="activecode" xml:id="review_loops">
            </program>

        </exercise>
    </subsection>
    <subsection>
        <title>Think About ...</title>
        <exercise xml:id="ex-loop-reflection">
            <statement>
                <p>When is a <c>for</c> loop a better choice than a <c>while</c> loop?</p>
            </statement>
            <response>
            </response>
        </exercise>
    </subsection>
</section>